.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet \- multi-account git-backed wallet store
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning wallet — multi-account git-backed wallet store.

Implements FEAT-174 + FEAT-193 (SQLite store) + FEAT-174's
git push/pull round-trip.

Subcommands:
  new <name>           initialise a new wallet repo
  use <name>           set the active wallet (writes ~/.lightning/active)
  list                 list wallets
  active               print active wallet name
  push [<remote>]      git push the wallet repo
  pull [<remote>]      git pull, then rebuild state.db
  sync [<remote>]      pull + push
  path                 print the active wallet's filesystem path
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning wallet <subcommand> [args]

subcommands:
   new <name>           initialise a new wallet repo
   use <name>           set the active wallet
   list                 list wallets
   active               print the active wallet name
   path                 print the active wallet's filesystem path
   push [<remote>]      git push the wallet repo
   pull [<remote>]      git pull + rebuild state.db
   sync [<remote>]      pull + push
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
